{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.20",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 20 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:1",
      "text": "Wine is a mocker and beer is a brawler. Whoever is led astray by them is not wise.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:2",
      "text": "The terror of a king is like the roaring of a lion. He who provokes him to anger forfeits his own life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:3",
      "text": "It is an honor for a man to keep aloof from strife, but every fool will be quarreling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:4",
      "text": "The sluggard will not plow by reason of the winter; therefore he shall beg in harvest, and have nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:5",
      "text": "Counsel in the heart of man is like deep water, but a man of understanding will draw it out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:6",
      "text": "Many men claim to be men of unfailing love, but who can find a faithful man?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:7",
      "text": "A righteous man walks in integrity. Blessed are his children after him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:8",
      "text": "A king who sits on the throne of judgment scatters away all evil with his eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:9",
      "text": "Who can say, “ I have made my heart pure. I am clean and without sin ”?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:10",
      "text": "Differing weights and differing measures, both of them alike are an abomination to Yahweh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:11",
      "text": "Even a child makes himself known by his doings, whether his work is pure, and whether it is right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:12",
      "text": "The hearing ear, and the seeing eye, Yahweh has made even both of them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:13",
      "text": "Don’t love sleep, lest you come to poverty. Open your eyes, and you shall be satisfied with bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:14",
      "text": "“ It ’s no good, it ’s no good,” says the buyer; but when he is gone his way, then he boasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:15",
      "text": "There is gold and abundance of rubies, but the lips of knowledge are a rare jewel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:16",
      "text": "Take the garment of one who puts up collateral for a stranger; and hold him in pledge for a wayward woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:17",
      "text": "Fraudulent food is sweet to a man, but afterwards his mouth is filled with gravel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:18",
      "text": "Plans are established by advice; by wise guidance you wage war!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:19",
      "text": "He who goes about as a tale-bearer reveals secrets; therefore don’t keep company with him who opens wide his lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:20",
      "text": "Whoever curses his father or his mother, his lamp shall be put out in blackness of darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:21",
      "text": "An inheritance quickly gained at the beginning won’t be blessed in the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:22",
      "text": "Don’t say, “ I will pay back evil.” Wait for Yahweh, and he will save you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:23",
      "text": "Yahweh detests differing weights, and dishonest scales are not pleasing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:24",
      "text": "A man ’s steps are from Yahweh; how then can man understand his way?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:25",
      "text": "It is a snare to a man to make a rash dedication, then later to consider his vows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:26",
      "text": "A wise king winnows out the wicked, and drives the threshing wheel over them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:27",
      "text": "The spirit of man is Yahweh ’s lamp, searching all his innermost parts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:28",
      "text": "Love and faithfulness keep the king safe. His throne is sustained by love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:29",
      "text": "The glory of young men is their strength. The splendor of old men is their gray hair.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.20.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:30",
      "text": "Wounding blows cleanse away evil, and beatings purge the innermost parts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
